 had to roll my eyes at him because, while he is a far cry from the corruption of these government officials, he spent a fair amount of time indulging in the get-rich-quick atmosphere of post-Soviet Russia himself. If he had gone farther to acknowledge some of his own privilege, that would've helped, but he can seem pretty oblivious at times. The voice does get better in the last few chapters of the book. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eI'm glad that I read this book and learned more about the unhinged corruption among Russia's oligarchs and government officials, but \"Red Notice\" is a long slog to get to the meat of this subject. A book of this topic should be focused directly on the true main characters of this issue - the activists and citizens who have been unjustly imprisoned and killed like Sergei Magnitsky. \u003cbr /\u003e","rating":2,"shelving":{"__typename":"Shelving","shelf":{"__typename":"Shelf","name":"read","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/12827795?shelf=read"},"taggings":[{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"memoirs","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/12827795?shelf=memoirs"}},{"__typename":"Tagging","tag":{"__typename":"Tag","name":"2017","webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/list/12827795?shelf=2017"}}],"webUrl":"https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2028324124"},"likeCount":45,"viewerHasLiked":null,"commentCount":4,"viewerCanComment({\"resourceType\":\"review\"})":null},"Contributor:kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.Jqe6ukyjAgYtpjFoh3ImFQ":{"id":"kca://author/amzn1.gr.author.v1.Jqe6ukyjAgYtpjFoh3ImFQ","__typename":"Contributor","works":{"__typename":"ContributorWorksConnection","totalCount":14}},"User:15921992":{"id":15921992,"__typename":"User","legacyId":15921992,"imageUrlSquare":"https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1356971705i/15921992._UX200_CR0,25,200,200_.jpg","isAuthor":true,"textReviewsCount":62,"viewableName":"Geza Tatrallyay","isBlockedByViewer":false,"